SIMPLE: skipjack
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Skipjack
<hw>Skip"jack`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An
upstart.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Ford.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An elater; a snap bug, or
snapping beetle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A name given to several kinds of
a fish, as the common bluefish, the alewife, the bonito, the butterfish,
the cutlass fish, the jurel, the leather jacket, the runner, the saurel,
the saury, the threadfish, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>A shallow sailboat with a
rectilinear or V-shaped cross section.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Skipper</ent>⟦br⟧
